# BC26 Base Symbols Reference

## Local Symbols Location

**Base Path:** `C:\Temp\BC26Objects` (1.7GB, ~27,220 AL files)

> ⚠️ Always use LOCAL symbols - MCP not trusted

## Available Modules

### Microsoft Base
- **BaseApp** - Microsoft Base Application (26.3.36158.37931)
  - Standard tables, pages, codeunits
  - Core BC functionality
- **ALAppExtensions** - Microsoft AL App Extensions
- **BCIntrastatCore** - Microsoft Intrastat Core (26.4.37194.37425)
- **BC-RS** - BC Reference Symbols

### Continia Modules
- ContiniaBusinessFoundation
- ContiniaConnectorApp (26.3.2.359795)
- ContiniaCore (26.3.3.359418)
- ContiniaDeliveryNetwork (26.3.1.355345)
- ContiniaDocumentCapture (26.3.3.360549)
- ContiniaDocumentOutput (26.3.0.361764)
- ContiniaSystemApplication (26.3.2.359795)

## Usage for Development

**Use base files for:**
- Standard object structure reference
- Field names and property patterns
- Event subscriber patterns
- Extension point verification
- Table/Page ID lookups

## When to Request Additional Modules

If you need modules not listed above:
- Other Microsoft extensions
- Third-party apps
- Specific BC modules

**Request from user BEFORE creating plans**

## Quick Reference Commands

```bash
# Find standard Customer table
C:\Temp\BC26Objects\BaseApp\Customer.Table.al

# Find Sales Order page
C:\Temp\BC26Objects\BaseApp\SalesOrder.Page.al

# Search for specific pattern
grep -r "OnAfterValidateEvent" C:\Temp\BC26Objects\BaseApp
```
